This is the series

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle 
\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{2n-1}
\end{align*}

Notice

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle 
\frac{1}{2n-1} > \frac{1}{2n} > 0
\end{align*}

for all $\displaystyle n$, and

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle 
\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{2n} = \frac{1}{2} \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{n}
\end{align*}

diverges by p-series (it's just a multiple of the harmonic series). Then
by the comparison test, the series

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle 
1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}+\frac{1}{9}+\cdots
\end{align*}

diverges.
